definitions.definition: singular of shenanigans : a deceitful confidence trick ; also, an act of mischief ; a prank , a trick ; an act of mischievous play , especially by children .
examples: I spotted his next shenanigan —saw it coming—and so avoided being fooled.

definitions.definition: Dishonest , underhanded , or unscrupulous activities or behaviour ; skulduggery , trickery ; also, mischievous behaviour or play; high jinks .

main_definition: ( countable , chiefly in the plural ) singular of shenanigans : a deceitful confidence trick ; also, an act of mischief ; a prank , a trick ; an act of mischievous play , especially by children .
secondary_definitions: ( uncountable , dated , rare ) Dishonest , underhanded , or unscrupulous activities or behaviour ; skulduggery , trickery ; also, mischievous behaviour or play; high jinks .
